Definition: an optical illusion of motion produced by viewing a rapid succession of still pictures of a moving object
Example: the cinema relies on apparent motion; the succession of flashing lights gave an illusion of movement
Synonyms: motion, apparent_movement, movement, optical_illusion, an, optical, illusion, of, produced, by, viewing, a, rapid, succession, still, pictures, moving, object, the, cinema, relies, on, apparent, flashing, lights, gave
Category: noun.phenomenon
